1
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:41,920
Here.

2
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,600
- Fill up the glasses.
- Here.

3
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:45,640
It's a good thing that
Qiangzi is going back home.

4
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,200
Why the long faces?

5
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,480
Let's drink. Come on.

6
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,240
I'm going back to
my hometown too.

7
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,840
Now that the
construction has stopped,

8
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,320
I can't even pay my rent.

9
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:02,040
I really regret not studying harder.
I applied for a security job.

10
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,160
Yet they didn't want me.

11
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:06,200
Mr. Jiao, you're going
back to your hometown too?

12
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:10,319
My daughter is about
to go to high school.

13
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:14,040
I have to find a way to pay for
her tuition and living expenses.

14
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:19,320
Also, she doesn't know about what
happened at the construction site.

15
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:20,640
If I go back,

16
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,440
she'll surely be distracted.

17
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,360
It might even affect how
she does on her exams.

18
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,360
Are you still living
in that garage?

19
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:29,080
It's starting to get hot.

20
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:31,280
There are no windows or
water. How can you live there?

21
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,640
It's just a place to sleep.

22
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:36,600
I'm planning to do deliveries
with my nephew in Old Town.

23
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,680
Why don't you try
it out with me?

24
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,640
Deliveries?

25
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:42,720
You don't know, do you?

26
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,240
Young people these days

27
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,320
have no time to buy anything.

28
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,600
They have to rely on others
to bring them food and drinks.

29
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,320
You're right.

30
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,840
That's what I do
to earn money now.

31
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,000
I only have
elementary education.

32
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,200
And I'm terrible at talking.

33
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,000
I'm not as smart as you.

34
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,080
You're clever.

35
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,560
I can't do it.

36
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,360
You just run errands
and find the addresses.

37
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,320
It's fine as long as you're
willing to work hard.

38
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,400
But to do this,

39
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:07,840
you'll need an electric scooter.

40
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,920
An electric scooter?

41
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,480
Get a used one.

42
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,200
Just save up 700 to 800 yuan

43
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,440
and buy a used one.

44
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,720
Mr. Jiang.

45
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,656
How much did you get for your
Good Samaritan Award last time?

46
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,680
I got 20,000.

47
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:28,160
Mr. Jiang, you've
hit the jackpot.

48
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,240
People like us

49
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,160
struggle to survive day-to-day.

50
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:33,016
- Utensils are two yuan.
- I don't dare to spend a penny of it.

51
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:36,280
- You can check on the Internet.
- Forget it. You're ripping me off.

52
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,816
- What are you talking about?
- Why are you charging for paper?

53
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,960
- We've been here so many times.
- What are you doing?

54
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,056
- No, she…
- Are you stupid?

55
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:43,400
- Qiangzi.
- Why are you fighting?

56
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,080
- Stop it, Qiangzi.
- Why are you arguing?

57
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,520
- Qiangzi.
- Come on, Qiangzi.

58
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,960
That's enough, Qiangzi.

59
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:50,360
- All right, knock it off.
- No.

60
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,800
- Did you pay her?
- Stop it.

61
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,320
- All right.
- Hey, Mr. Jiang.

62
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,680
Everything costs money.

63
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,680
KNOW YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES
AS A LANDLORD

64
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:06,080
STOP ILLEGAL
HABITATION OF GARAGES

65
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:21,320
CLAMPING DOWN ON THOSE
ILLEGALLY LIVING IN GARAGES

66
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:10,240
Mr. Jiao, you're finally back.

67
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:14,880
You're a hard man to find.

68
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:17,920
I've been looking for you for three
days, but you were nowhere to be found.

69
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,640
Sir.

70
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:22,840
I've been busy at the
construction site.

71
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,840
Okay.

72
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:27,400
Pack up and move out.

73
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,800
We're running out of time.

74
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:33,600
I can get the money for
the rent in two days.

75
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,000
It's not about the rent.

76
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:38,000
The residents' committee
has informed us.

77
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,040
All garages can no
longer be rented out.

78
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:42,440
Why not?

79
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:46,280
They are going to check out the
rental situation of all the garages.

80
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,641
If they find anyone living in
one, we'll be fined heavily.

81
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,600
How could I dare to
let you stay here?

82
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:54,280
Pay the rent,

83
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,720
pack your things, and leave.

84
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,040
Sir.

85
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,280
This is all I have.

86
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:32,720
Give me two more days.

87
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,280
I'll move as soon
as I find a place.

88
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:37,200
This is only enough
for last month's rent.

89
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:40,096
You stayed for one extra week,
but I won't ask for that money.

90
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,696
Still, you have to
move out immediately.

91
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,440
The inspectors
will be here soon.

92
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,000
There's no time.

93
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:50,880
If I had a place to move, I
would have already done it.

94
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,400
Here.

95
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,120
Take it.

96
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,960
I really can't let you live
in this garage anymore.

97
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:06,480
This bit of money
is not worth it.

98
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,440
Mr. Jiao.

99
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,640
Please understand.

100
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,640
It's hard for all of us, right?

101
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,120
GANGWU NEW VILLAGE STOP

