That's true.

114
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,440
This suitcase

115
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,480
is a bit difficult to check.

116
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,320
The plastic bag is
probably easier.

117
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:03,320
Why don't we start
with her this time?

118
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,240
Okay.

119
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,800
I'll do it this time.

120
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,680
Ma'am.

121
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,520
Ma'am.

122
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:28,800
Do you have a
sanitary pad with you?

123
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,160
My period is here.

124
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,440
I don't have one with me.
I'd like to borrow one.

125
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:33,640
No.

126
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,200
No?

127
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:40,200
But I think I saw
some in your bag.

128
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,160
That's why I asked you. You…

129
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,520
I'm sorry.

130
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,440
I probably mistook the bag
inside for the packaging.

131
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,520
I'm sorry.

132
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,920
Ma'am, why did you bring a pot?

133
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,920
What's inside?

134
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,440
It looked heavy when you
brought it on the bus.

135
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,960
I'm curious about what's inside.

136
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,160
Meat.

137
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:14,720
Meat.

138
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,280
Stewed meat in a
pressure cooker?

139
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,680
Sorry for disturbing you.

140
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,480
Weren't you too straightforward?

141
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,400
Don't you find it strange?

142
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,920
Who carries food in a
pot when they go out?

143
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,560
Don't they use
insulated lunch boxes?

144
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,640
Our family carries
meat in a pot.

145
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:38,120
When I was in college, my mom
used to bring us a pot of meat.

146
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,280
It's very normal.

147
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,840
If that's the case,

148
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:48,160
she can be cleared of suspicion.

149
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,520
Did you smell it?

150
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,600
Any smell of meat?

151
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,200
I think I smelled something,

152
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:01,040
but I can't tell
what the smell is.

153
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:07,200
It might be a spice
in the stewed meat.

154
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:19,080
When you grabbed her things just now,
she didn't really have any reaction.

155
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,520
Maybe it's really not her.

156
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,320
If it's not her,

157
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,800
then don't we…

158
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:33,120
already have a conclusion?

159
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,760
But how do we
check the suitcase?

160
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,440
When the door opens
at the next stop,

161
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,720
just throw the suitcase off.

162
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,080
Let's take a gamble.

163
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,160
What if we're wrong?

164
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,680
If we're wrong…

165
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:56,240
The loop this time has moved
up to Gangwu New Village stop.

166
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,120
The next loop will
still shift earlier.

167
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:01,080
Then we'll just stop that
lady outside the bus.

168
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:20,360
NEXT STOP, YANJIANG EAST ROAD

169
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:24,040
YANJIANG EAST ROAD STOP

170
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,880
<i>We've arrived at
Yanjiang East Road.</i>

171
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:38,640
<i>Please exit through
the rear door.</i>

172
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,240
<i>Please tap your
card when exiting.</i>

173
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,960
<i>Please mind the doors.</i>

174
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,440
What's going on? Are you okay?

175
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,640
CERTIFICATE OF MERIT

176
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,000
JIAO JIAO, FIRST PLACE IN THE
MIDDLE SCHOOL MATH OLYMPIAD

177
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,080
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

178
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:45,320
Hurry and get off.

179
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,480
Excuse me, coming through.

180
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,960
Run!

181
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:35,400
Mr. Jiao.

182
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,000
Here's a suitcase.

183
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,880
You can use it.

184
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,920
Don't worry about it. It's old.

185
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,560
I'll throw it away
if you don't use it.

186
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,280
Thank you.

187
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:56,920
Are there things inside?

188
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:00,800
We must've forgotten to clean it out
after my wife and I went on a trip.

189
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,920
Take whatever is useful to
you. Throw the rest out.

190
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:09,920
Hello.

191
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:13,880
Are they coming to our
neighborhood in the afternoon?

192
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,440
Have they inspected
your neighborhood?

193
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:18,920
Did they really fine you?

194
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,600
They really did?

195
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,120
How much is the fine?

196
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,600
The rent we get every
month is so little.

197
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,760
Now that we're getting fined,
it was all for nothing.

198
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,200
Okay.

199
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:44,760
Mr. Jiao.

200
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,920
I really don't mean to
put you on the spot.

201
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:50,200
Every time the residents'
committee came to do inspections,

202
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,240
I managed to fool them.

203
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,200
But the fire department
is coming this time.

204
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,440
I'll be fined if I get caught.

205
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:58,800
I can't help it.

206
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:01,120
I'm sorry.

207
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:12,320
Do you have a place to stay?

208
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:18,480
I have a colleague who
lives across the river.

209
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:20,120
I'll ask him for help.

210
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,360
CERTIFICATE OF MERIT

211
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,200
CERTIFICATE OF MERIT

212
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,200
Jiaojiao.

213
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,240
Listen to me.

214
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,280
You have to study hard.

215
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:48,720
Don't think too much.

216
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,280
I'm fine here.

217
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,080
I'll work hard to earn
more money for us.

218
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,200
From now on, if you need
anything, just tell me.

219
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,320
Whether they are sanitary
pads or cleansers,

220
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,600
we can afford it.

221
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:02,080
<i>Will you stop
talking about that?</i>

222
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,920
<i>Dad, I really don't want
to go to school anymore.</i>

223
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,319
<i>School costs money.</i>

224
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:08,480
<i>I went to town and asked.</i>

225
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:09,720
<i>I can get a job.</i>

226
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:11,000
<i>Let's work together.</i>

227
00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:12,520
<i>We'll be able to
pay off your debt.</i>

228
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:14,079
Okay, that's enough!

229
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:17,400
Pay off my debt? I already told
you to stop bringing that up.

230
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:19,240
Stop worrying about that.

231
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:20,920
You have to go to
school tomorrow.

232
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,599
If you don't go, I'll teach
you a lesson when I get back.

233
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:25,079
Hello?

234
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,160
Hello?

235
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:40,960
<i>Hello.</i>

236
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,640
<i>The person you are trying
to reach is currently busy.</i>

237
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,400
<i>Please try again later.</i>

238
